1. Mutual Exclusion: Each philosopher needs to pick up both forks to eat, which means only one philosopher can use a pair of forks at a time, enforcing mutual exclusion.

2. Hold and Wait: Philosophers may hold onto one fork while waiting for another philosopher to release their fork. This condition leads to philosophers blocking each other, causing deadlock.

